# VoxScript-first automation

## Policy

All project automation MUST be `.vox` files executed via `vox run`. Do **not** create new `.ps1`, `.sh`, or `.py` scripts for project automation.

```
# Correct — cross-platform, type-checked, telemetry-observable
vox run scripts/corpus-prep.vox

# Correct — fast interpreter tier, no compile step
vox run --interp scripts/compute-config.vox

# WRONG — do not introduce new shell scripts
# pwsh -File scripts/my-new-pipeline.ps1
# python scripts/my-transform.py
# bash scripts/my-setup.sh
```

## Execution tiers

| Need | Command |
|---|---|
| Pure computation | `vox run --interp` |
| File I/O or subprocess | `vox run` (native, cached) |
| Untrusted execution | `vox run --isolation wasm` |

## Bootstrap exception

`scripts/windows/vox-dev.ps1` and `scripts/vox-dev.sh` are **exempt** — they are thin (≤10 line) forwarders that run `cargo run -p vox-cli` before `vox` is built. No new logic may be added to these files.

## Security invariants

- Scripts modifying the repo MUST be committed to VCS before agent execution
- Subprocess calls use `vox-runtime` process primitives (telemetry-observable)
- Secrets via vox-secrets only (`vox_secrets::resolve_secret(...)`)

